19 "Article 9.
20 "Debt Adjusting.Adjusting and Debt Settlement Prohibited.
21 "§ 75-151. Definitions.
22 As used in this Article, the following definitions apply:
23 (1) "Debt adjuster" means a person who engages in, attempts to engage in, or
24 offers to engage in the practice or business of debt adjusting.
25 (1) Affiliate. – Any person that controls, is controlled by, or is under common
26 control with any other person.
27 (2) "Debt adjusting" means entering Debt adjusting. – Entering into or making a
28 contract, express or implied, with a particular debtor whereby the debtor
29 agrees to pay a certain amount of money periodically to the person engaged
30 in the debt adjusting business and that person, for consideration, agrees to
31 distribute, or distributes the same among certain specified one or more
32 creditors in accordance with a plan agreed upon. Debt adjusting includes the
33 business or practice of any person who holds himself out as acting or offering
34 or attempting to act for consideration as an intermediary between a debtor and
35 his creditors for the purpose of settling, compounding, or in any way altering
36 the terms of payment of any debt of a debtor, and to that end receives money
