1 or other property from the debtor, or on behalf of the debtor, for the payment
2 to, or distribution among, the creditors of the debtor.
3 (3) Debt adjusting also includes the business or practice of debt settlement or
4 foreclosure assistance whereby Debt settlement. – The business whereby any
5 person holds himself or herself themselves out as acting for consideration as
6 an intermediary between a debtor and one or more of the debtor's creditors for
7 the purpose of reducing, settling, or altering the terms of the payment of any
8 debt of the debtor, whether or not the person distributes the debtor's funds or
9 property among the creditors, and receives a fee or other consideration for
10 reducing, settling, or altering the terms of the payment of the debt in advance
11 of the debt settlement having been completed or in advance of all the services
12 agreed to having been rendered in full.debtor.
13 (3)(4) "Debtor" means an Debtor. – An individual who resides in North Carolina,
14 and includes two or more individuals who are jointly and severally, or jointly
15 or severally, indebted to a creditor or creditors.
16 (3a) "Nominal consideration" means a fee or a contribution to cover the cost of
17 administering a debt management plan not to exceed forty dollars ($40.00) for
18 origination or setup of the debt management plan and ten percent (10%) of the
19 monthly payment disbursed under the debt management plan, not to exceed
20 forty dollars ($40.00) per month.
21 (4)(5) "Person" means an Person. – An individual, firm, partnership, limited
22 partnership, corporation, or association.association, or other entity.
23 "§ 75-152. Debt adjusting and debt settlement prohibited.
24 No person, directly or through affiliates, shall engage in, offer to engage in, or attempt to
25 engage in debt adjusting or debt settlement.
26 "§ 75-153. Engaging, etc., in business of debt adjusting Debt adjusting and debt settlement
27 a misdemeanor.
28 If any Any person shall engage that engages in, or offer offers to engage in, or attempt to,
29 attempts to engage in the business or practice of debt adjusting, or if any person shall hereafter
30 act, offer to act, or attempt to act as a debt adjuster, he shall be adjusting or debt settlement is
31 guilty of a Class 2 misdemeanor.
32 "§ 75-154. Enjoining practice of debt adjusting; appointment of receiver for money and
33 property employed.Jurisdiction of the superior court to enjoin debt adjusting or
34 debt settlement.
35 (a) The superior court shall have has jurisdiction, in an action brought in the name of the
36 State by the Attorney General or the district attorney of the prosecutorial district as defined in
37 G.S. 7A-60, to enjoin, as an unfair or deceptive trade practice, the continuation of any debt
38 adjusting or debt settlement business or the offering of any debt adjusting services. or debt
39 settlement services in violation of this Article.
40 (b) The Attorney General or the district attorney who brings an action under this section
41 may appoint a receiver for the property and money employed in the transaction of business by
42 such the person as a debt adjuster, to ensure, so far as may be possible, the return to debtors of
43 so much of their money and property as has been received by the debt adjuster, and has not been
44 paid to the creditors of the debtors.
45 (c) The court in an action under this section may also assess civil penalties under
46 G.S. 75-15.2 and award attorneys' fees to the State under G.S. 75-16.1.
47 (d) This section is in addition to any other remedies available under this Chapter or other
48 laws.
49 "§ 75-155. Certain persons and transactions not deemed debt adjusters or debt
50 adjustment.Acts authorized.
